MBOMBELA &#8211; Students are increasingly turning to online institutions to obtain tertiary qualifications. This has produced a new Internet scam: the online bogus qualification.The Department of Higher Education and Training (DHET) is concerned about this growth of fraudulent online universities and colleges.Dr Shaheeda Essack, deputy director of private higher education from DHET told Lowvelder on Friday that this worldwide trend in education fraud has perhaps found a foothold in Mpumalanga.She warned students who seek study opportunities against an allegedly fraudulent private online college, Watchman University of Theology (Pty) Ltd.